description:
Hmmmm I had high hopes coming here cause I really liked the convenient location and from the pics on yelp the decor and atmosphere seemed totally my cup of tea but my overall experience was alright. 

I think this would be a cool place to come with a big group of friends since they have large tables upstairs with ample room and a nice wood finish. I probably would come here again if a friend wanted to grab a beer in the sunset because I really liked the open layout but would I come here for their awesome selection of beer? =P Nope! I get that as a brewing company you want to serve your own personal brews but I think you should have more than one guest beer. I personally love to choose from a wide selection but when I only get to choose from 5 different choices it makes me a bit sad. It's like being a guy and getting all dressed up to go to a club and the ratio is like 10:1. Disappointing I say! Hopefully they'll expand their number of guest beers if enough people complain about it. =P I ended up getting the extra pale ale which I did like but then again I think I've only disliked 2 beers in my entire lifetime. n_n;;; 

Waiters were super friendly though which is why I bumped up my review to 3 stars! They were super chill and okay with me being the annoying chick who keeps switching tables cause she doesn't know how big her party is. n_n;; I didn't get a chance to try the food so maybe next time. =D
